Direct Known Subclasses:
InMemoryFeatureSet, LazyFeatureSet
public abstract class FeatureSet
extends AbstractMolSet<FeatureSet>
implements MolSetInterface<FeatureSet,Feature>

A feature set is a set (ex: collection, bag) of features. A feature set cannot exist without a reference even if the reference is ad hoc and/or user-created. Immutable (but tags are not). TODO: Should we consider deleting Features from FeatureSets as well as adding them or can that be implicit when a Feature itself is deleted?
